### рџ”ґ BUG #1 вЂ” Cookie / Cross-Origin: `SameSite=None` Requires `Secure`, But Render May Not Forward It Correctly

**Severity: Critical**

**Affected Files:**
- [server/utils/cookieHelpers.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/utils/cookieHelpers.js)
- [server/server.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/server.js)

**What the code does:**
```js
// cookieHelpers.js
sameSite: isProd ? "none" : "lax",
secure: isProd,
```

**Why it fails:**

The app is deployed cross-domain:
- Frontend: `https://url-shortener-lovat-gamma.vercel.app` (Vercel)
- Backend: `https://url-shortener-api-9ucd.onrender.com` (Render)

For cookies to be sent cross-domain, `SameSite=None; Secure` is **required**. This is correctly set in [cookieHelpers.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/utils/cookieHelpers.js).

However, **the cookie has no explicit `domain` set**. When `domain` is omitted, cookies are scoped to the backend's domain only (`url-shortener-api-9ucd.onrender.com`). The browser **will** send this cookie back to Render on subsequent requests вЂ” this part is correct.

**The real issue is the `path` attribute.** No `path` is set on the cookie, so it defaults to the path from which it was issued. If the refresh endpoint is at `/api/auth/refresh` and the cookie was issued on `/api/auth/login`, the **path scope** might restrict cookie delivery. Always explicitly set `path: "/"`.

**Additionally:** Many modern browsers (Safari, Firefox with Strict ETP, Brave) **block third-party cookies entirely**, even with `SameSite=None; Secure`. Since the frontend is on Vercel and the backend is on Render вЂ” these are different domains, not just subdomains вЂ” cookies will be **silently blocked** for a significant percentage of users.

**Recommended Fix:**
```js
// cookieHelpers.js вЂ” add path: "/"
res.cookie("accessToken", accessToken, {
  ...opts,
  path: "/",         // в†ђ ADD THIS
  maxAge: ACCESS_TOKEN_MAX_AGE,
});
res.cookie("refreshToken", refreshToken, {
  ...opts,
  path: "/",         // в†ђ ADD THIS
  maxAge: REFRESH_TOKEN_MAX_AGE,
});
```

For browsers that block third-party cookies: switch to an **Authorization header + localStorage** strategy instead of cookie-based auth, OR proxy the backend through the same Vercel domain to make them same-site. The current architecture has a fundamental cross-site cookie limitation that **cannot be fully solved with cookie flags alone**.

