### рџ”ґ BUG #2 вЂ” Login Persistence: `sessionStorage` Clears on Tab/Browser Close

**Severity: Critical**

**Affected Files:**
- [client/services/api.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/services/api.js) (lines 12, 45, 52)
- [client/src/home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) (line 162)

**What the code does:**
```js
// api.js вЂ” token saved to sessionStorage
sessionStorage.setItem("token", newToken);

// home.jsx logout
sessionStorage.removeItem("token");
```

**Why it fails:**
`sessionStorage` is **session-scoped** вЂ” it is automatically cleared when the browser tab or window is closed. The requirement is for the user to stay logged in for **7 days**, but using `sessionStorage` means:
- Every tab close = logged out
- Every browser restart = logged out
- Navigating away and back = logged out (in some scenarios)

The refresh token cookie is correctly set with a 7-day `maxAge`, but the access token stored in `sessionStorage` is wiped immediately on tab close. On the next visit, the app has no token, calls `/api/auth/me`, gets a 401, then tries to refresh вЂ” but that refresh flow itself relies on the cookie being present AND the browser not blocking it (see Bug #1).

**Recommended Fix:**
Replace `sessionStorage` with `localStorage` for token persistence across sessions:
```js
// api.js
localStorage.setItem("token", newToken);
// ...
localStorage.removeItem("token");

// home.jsx logout
localStorage.removeItem("token");
```

