### рџ”ґ BUG #3 вЂ” OAuth Callback: Access Token Exposed in URL Query String

**Severity: Critical**

**Affected Files:**
- [server/routes/authRoutes.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/routes/authRoutes.js) (lines 74, 105)
- [client/src/authCallback.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/authCallback.jsx)

**What the code does:**
```js
// authRoutes.js вЂ” OAuth callback
return res.redirect(`${process.env.CLIENT_URL}/auth/callback?token=${accessToken}`);
```

```jsx
// authCallback.jsx вЂ” callback handler
// вќ— token from URL is NEVER read or used
await api.post("/api/auth/refresh", {}, { skipAuthRefresh: true });
const res = await api.get("/api/auth/me", { skipAuthRefresh: true });
```

**Why it fails (two issues):**

**Issue A вЂ” Security:** The access token (a valid JWT) is placed in the URL. This means:
- It appears in browser history
- It is logged in server access logs
- It can be captured by any third-party script that reads `document.referrer` or `window.location`
- Referrer headers leak it to any external resources on the page

**Issue B вЂ” Functional bug:** The [authCallback.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/authCallback.jsx) component **never reads `?token` from the URL**. It ignores the token entirely and just calls `/api/auth/refresh` + `/api/auth/me`. This only works if the cookie was successfully set **before** the redirect вЂ” which requires the `Set-Cookie` on the OAuth redirect response to be honored by the browser. In cross-domain deployments, many browsers do NOT honor `Set-Cookie` on redirect responses, causing the auth callback to fail silently and redirect users to `/login`.

The `token` from `searchParams` (imported and destructured in [authCallback.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/authCallback.jsx)) is **never used**:
```jsx
const [searchParams] = useSearchParams();  // searchParams never queried!
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Read the token from the URL, store it in `localStorage`, and set it as the Authorization header вЂ” avoiding cookie dependency for OAuth:
```jsx
// authCallback.jsx
const token = searchParams.get("token");
if (token) {
  localStorage.setItem("token", token);
}
navigate("/", { replace: true });
```

And remove the token from the URL redirect long-term by using a short-lived PKCE-style state parameter pattern.

