### рџ”ґ BUG #4 вЂ” App Init: Silent Refresh Fires But Result Never Updates State

**Severity: Critical**

**Affected Files:**
- [client/src/App.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/App.jsx) (lines 137вЂ“142)

**What the code does:**
```jsx
// App.jsx
useEffect(() => {
  api
    .post("/api/auth/refresh", {}, { skipAuthRefresh: true })
    .catch(() => {});  // в†ђ result completely ignored
}, []);
```

**Why it fails:**
The intention is to silently refresh the access token on app load so the user doesn't have to log in again. However:

1. The refresh response contains a `token` in `res.data.token` вЂ” this is **never stored** anywhere (not in `localStorage`, not in `sessionStorage`).
2. The refresh endpoint also rotates the refresh token and sets new cookies via `Set-Cookie` вЂ” but due to cross-site cookie blocking (Bug #1), this may not work.
3. Even if the refresh succeeds, the new access token is discarded. So when [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) then calls `/api/auth/me`, it still has no access token and gets a 401.

**The refresh fires but achieves nothing.** The UI's `isAuthenticated` state in [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) is determined by a separate [checkAuth()](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx#178-189) call using `{ skipAuthRefresh: true }`, which means if the token is expired, it will fail and set the user as unauthenticated вЂ” even though a perfectly valid refresh token exists.

**Recommended Fix:**
```jsx
// App.jsx
useEffect(() => {
  api
    .post("/api/auth/refresh", {}, { skipAuthRefresh: true })
    .then((res) => {
      const newToken = res.data?.token;
      if (newToken) {
        localStorage.setItem("token", newToken);  // persist it!
      }
    })
    .catch(() => {}); // silently fail if no session
}, []);
```

