### рџџ  BUG #5 вЂ” Environment Variables: Local [.env](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/.env) Has Wrong API Base URL

**Severity: Medium**

**Affected Files:**
- [client/.env](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/.env) (line 1)

**What the code does:**
```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

**Why it fails:**
[api.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/services/api.js) creates an Axios instance with:
```js
const BASE_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL;
const api = axios.create({ baseURL: BASE_URL });
```

Then calls are made like:
```js
api.post("/api/auth/login", ...)
api.get("/api/auth/me", ...)
```

If `VITE_API_URL` is already `http://localhost:5000/api`, then the full URL becomes:
```
http://localhost:5000/api/api/auth/login  в†ђ DOUBLE /api !
```

The `VITE_API_URL` should be the base server URL **without** the `/api` path:
```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

On Vercel (from the screenshot), it is set to:
```
VITE_API_URL=https://url-shortener-api-9ucd.onrender.com
```
This Vercel value is **correct** вЂ” no `/api` suffix. But the local dev [.env](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/.env) has `/api` in it, causing all API calls to fail during local development with double-prefixed paths.

**Recommended Fix:**
```env
# client/.env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000
```

