### рџџ  BUG #8 вЂ” Home Auth Check Bypasses Interceptor Refresh

**Severity: Medium**

**Affected Files:**
- [client/src/home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) (lines 177вЂ“190)

**What the code does:**
```jsx
// home.jsx
const res = await api.get("/api/auth/me", { skipAuthRefresh: true });
```

**Why it fails:**
The [checkAuth()](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx#178-189) in [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) passes `{ skipAuthRefresh: true }` вЂ” this means when the access token is expired and `/api/auth/me` returns 401, the **interceptor will NOT attempt to refresh**. The user will be immediately marked as unauthenticated.

This is fine on the Dashboard route (where the full [ProtectedRoute](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/App.jsx#106-133) loop handles auth), but in [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) it means a user who has a valid refresh token but an expired access token will **see the Login button instead of their avatar**, even though they are technically still logged in.

Compare this to [ProtectedRoute](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/App.jsx#106-133) in [App.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/App.jsx):
```jsx
await api.get("/api/auth/me");  // в†ђ no skipAuthRefresh, interceptor CAN refresh
```

The [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) auth check should also allow the interceptor to do its job.

**Recommended Fix:**
Remove `{ skipAuthRefresh: true }` from the [home.jsx](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/src/home.jsx) auth check:
```jsx
const res = await api.get("/api/auth/me");  // let interceptor handle refresh
```

