### рџџЎ BUG #11 вЂ” Unused `express-session` Middleware

**Severity: Minor**

**Affected Files:**
- [server/server.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/server.js) (lines 108вЂ“127)
- [server/package.json](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/package.json) (implied dependency)

**What the code does:**
```js
app.use(session({
  secret: process.env.SESSION_SECRET,
  resave: false,
  saveUninitialized: false,
  store: MongoStore.create({ mongoUrl: mongoUri, ttl: 10 * 60 }),
  cookie: { httpOnly: true, secure: isProd, sameSite: ..., maxAge: 10 * 60 * 1000 },
  name: "sid",
}));
```

**Why it's a problem:**
The auth system is **fully JWT/cookie based**. Passport is initialized with `session: false` in the OAuth callbacks. No route uses `req.session`. The `express-session` middleware:
- Creates an unnecessary MongoDB write on every request (for session tracking)
- Emits a `sid` cookie alongside the auth cookies (confusing)
- Adds `MongoStore` overhead
- Has no effect on any application logic

This is dead code from an earlier implementation that wasn't cleaned up.

**Recommended Fix:**
Remove `express-session` and `connect-mongo` entirely from [server.js](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/server/server.js) and [package.json](file:///e:/p/url_shortner/client/package.json).

